HEADWORD: Smithsonite
<hw>Smith"son*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Smithsonian</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Native zinc
carbonate. It generally occurs in stalactitic, reniform, or botryoidal
shapes, of a white to gray, green, or brown color. See Note under
<er>Calamine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

